            . I live at Wandsworth. On the 13th of August, about four o'clock in the afternoon, I was in <placeName id="t18320906-108-crimeloc611">King-street, Smithfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-108-crimeloc611" type="placeName" value="King-street, Smithfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-108-crimeloc611" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-108-off609 t18320906-108-crimeloc611"></join>, and felt my handkerchief drawn from my pocket - I turned round, and saw the prisoner close to me, and the handkerchief on the ground, between us; it was impossible any body but him could have done it; as I stooped to take it up, he ran away, and was stopped by a gentleman, without my losing sight of him.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-108-person986">
